                <h1>William Shakespeare: A Brief Biography</h1>
                <p>William Shakespeare, born in 1564 in Stratford-upon-Avon, England, is renowned as one of the greatest playwrights and poets in history. His works, including "Hamlet," "Romeo and Juliet," and "Macbeth," explore timeless themes of love, power, and betrayal. He influenced the English language and culture significantly before his death in 1616.</p>
